en_60136_0	Three persons have been reported missing after a boat capsized in the Kalu Ganga in the Malwala area in Ratnapura.
en_60136_1	According to Acting Police Media Spokesperson SSP Prishantha Jayakodi the boat had toppled this morning.
en_60136_2	Out of the 10 people who were onboard at the time of the incident, seven have been rescued.
en_60136_3	SSP Jayakodi went on to say that the three missing persons are of the same family and search operations have commenced to rescue the missing victims.
en_60136_4	The incident had taken place when the group was returning after attending a funeral in the Malwala area.
en_60136_5	The victims are residents of Negombo.
en_60136_6	The Department of Meteorology states that showers may be experienced in the Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central & Southern regions of the island today.
en_60136_7	The Department of Meteorology has called upon the public to take precautions to minimise the damages caused by lightning as showers or thundershowers are expected today as well.
en_60136_8	Duty Meteorologist at the Met.
en_60136_9	Department Pabodini Karunapala said fairly heavy rains and strong winds are expected in certain parts of the country due to the South Western monsoon.
